"06/07/2020 08:30am","85.146.178.248","0","0031687639054","mattepascale@gmail.com ","12-11-1991","En couple","Chef Cuisinier","1681 PA (Chef Cuisinier  Cuisinier Privé Genève)","My name is Matteo Pascale, I am 28 years old, currently living in Amsterdam and originally from Italy and I am applying for the position of Chef Cuisinier.

As you can see from my attached curriculum vitae, I am originally trained in Italian cuisine and have worked in different international restaurants and hotels where I have acquired top level experience.

While working at the &Moshik** Michelin restaurant as a chef de partie I learned about classic French and modern Asian techniques using international ingredients. After two years, I became Junior Sous Chef and I was in charge of the hot section and overlooking all the cuisson, sauces and hot garnishes.

In addition, I was also responsible for placing all kitchen ingredients orders while being conscious of the food cost, and taking care of inventory. I also enjoyed the opportunity to present some of the dishes to the guests, which involved plating and explaining the dish in English, French or Italian, and transmitting to them my passion of food.

Currently, I work as chef de partie at Spectrum** Michelin Restaurant in the Waldorf Astoria Amsterdam, where I am deepening my knowledge of the field of luxury dining in hotels, and discover more traditional Asian techniques, mixed with Latin American and Dutch flavors.

Therefore, having refined my technique, knowledge and taste at a Michelin level, I will be proud to work as a Chef Cuisinier Privé,  taking care of the family’s preferences, always bringing my respect of the product, specially organic ingredients because I am big supporter of Km0 ingredients, supporting regional production.

Thank you for taking the time to read my application. I hope to hear back from you soon. 

Best regards,
Matteo Pascale
